article.headline: Vermont 71, Stony Brook 58
article.story: BURLINGTON, Vt. (AP) -- Josh Duell scored 14 points Wednesday as Vermont defeated Stony Brook, 71-58. Stony Brook (4-17, 2-9) lead 28-26 at the half before UVM (10-11, 6-5) settled down. Chris Holm had five points in a 9-0 run in the first three minutes of the second half as Vermont took control. Holm, scoreless in the opening 20 minutes, finished with nine points in the second half while Duell chipped in with eight. In addition to Duell and Holm, Colin McIntosh had his finest game for UVM with 13 points and six rebounds. Mike Trimboli also talled 13 points. For Stony Brook, Mitchell Beauford contributed 16 points. Mike Popoko and Bobby Santiago each added 10 points.
